10 EPISODES · ORIGINAL

Premiere: March 12, 2022

After her rise to superstardom, Addison Rae is returning to her roots in Louisiana. As she heads home for the first time since achieving Hollywood success, Addison will show fans a more personal side than they have ever seen before.

Starring - Addison Rae

Executive Producers - Jessica Sebastian

Co- Executive Producer - Maritza Navarro

Produced By - Maven

8 EPISODES · ORIGINAL

Premiere: Feburary 19, 2022

With multiple Grammys to her name, including Best New Artist, Megan Thee Stallion commands the charts, popular culture, and now Snapchat! In this new series, she’ll be joined by celebrity friends and their pets hosted in a way that only Megan can.

Starring - Megan Thee Stallion

Produced By - Westbrook Media

SEASON 1 · 6 EPISODES · ORIGINAL

Premiere: July 25, 2021

Six young people invite us into their lives as they share the next milestone in their coming out journey, supported by one of the most-loved icons in the LGBTQ+ community, Manny MUA.

Starring - Manny MUA

Produced By - 44 Blue Productions and Treetop Pictures

Executive Producers - Chloë Grace Moretz, Trevor Duke

SEASON 1 · 8 EPISODES · ORIGINAL

Premiere: June 4, 2021

Trippie Redd is on a journey to experience firsthand the major issues gripping our country today, from drug addiction to police reform, with the help of fellow celebrity friends who have a personal stake just like the rest of us.

Starring - Trippie Redd

Produced By - Trooper Entertainment

Executive Producers - Dave Caplan, Gary Ousdahl, Jason Bergh, Charlene Bryant, Trippe Redd

SEASON 1 · 6 EPISODES · ORIGINAL

Premiere: May 28, 2021

A first person series about Asian-Americans, from their own point of view, meant to challenge and break down stereotypes, address ongoing discrimination, hate crimes and terrorism, while also shedding light on and celebrating the diverse experience of being Asian-American in 2021 America.

Produced By - Barcroft Studios and Calico

Executive Producers - John Farrar, Danny Lee, Katie Spedding
